ric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>You take two cleircs.<P>3 bouts<P>Each bout, the GM Spawns two 44th level NPC of a random class.  The NPCs will be healable/buffable by players.  Each cleric is assigned an NPC.  No lead time to buff the NPC is given.  Clerics are allowed to give themselves any two buffs of their choice and remed before the match begins (and before the NPCs are spawned so they do not know in advance what they will face).<P>Winning "team" gets a point.  <BR>Winning "team" gets a second point if their NPC survived.<BR>Death of the cleirc constitutes automatic loss of the bout.<P>This contest will pit cleircs in a variety of situations as the get random classes (could be warrior/warrior, could be chanter/necro.  <P>The cleric must decide when to heal/nuke/root/stun.  <P>A prety fair test of our capabilities.<P>P.S.<BR>Just my personal note but I think it's pretty crappy of verant to have these contests at a time when those who have completed their epic quests in a rush have such a huge advantage.<P>P.P.S.  <BR>Dueling cleircs?  What a joke.  Sheesh.  Can the test be any further from the skills they we work to build?  So the cleircs all get up to 200 MR and blow all mana and the winning cleirc is the one wearing the FBSS and an uberweapon that any decent cleirc would have foregone and given to their guildmates.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lenia-EMarr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think the ultimate test would be to put a cleric in a group with a nuker that nukes right off the bat, a druid that tanks, a paladin that doesnt know the meaning of taunt, umm, a necro that goes afk and then falls asleep at the keyboard, a fatty sk that doesnt know the meaning of assist while the chanter is trying to ae mez the hordes of incoming that the monk puller forgot to fd pull on. Oh wait thats a typical night in Karnors  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P></FON